{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17621011","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17621011"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:47:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:47:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16663"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16663"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,1,0,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9354"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66198"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9354","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9354"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16663"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51646"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"38"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1091"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3029"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5524"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22142"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22143"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66198","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66198"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner for review of chronic headaches. When asked about home life, she becomes tearful and mentions that her partner tracks her location constantly, controls their finances, and has recently started pushing and shoving her during arguments. She says she is afraid to go home but has nowhere else to go.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes this presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Physical assault between strangers","Pattern of abusive and controlling behaviours within an intimate relationship","Mutual conflict requiring relationship counselling","Normal relationship stress response","Situational anger management issue"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct definition is that intimate partner violence represents a \u003Cstrong\u003Epattern of abusive and controlling behaviours within an intimate relationship\u003C/strong\u003E. This includes physical, emotional, psychological, and sexual abuse, as well as economic control. The pattern is typically ongoing and escalating rather than consisting of isolated incidents.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent common misconceptions:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhysical assault between strangers\u003C/strong\u003E fails to recognise the intimate relationship context and ongoing nature of the abuse.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMutual conflict requiring relationship counselling\u003C/strong\u003E inappropriately suggests shared responsibility and could place the victim at increased risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal relationship stress response\u003C/strong\u003E dangerously minimises abusive behaviour that requires intervention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESituational anger management issue\u003C/strong\u003E overlooks the systematic pattern of power and control that characterises intimate partner violence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers should be aware that intimate partner violence affects people of all genders, though women are disproportionately impacted. It is important to screen for intimate partner violence and provide appropriate support and referrals.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Intimate partner violence affects approximately 1 in 4 women globally during their lifetime.","Physical violence, psychological abuse, sexual coercion, and controlling behaviours are the main types of intimate partner violence.","Healthcare providers have an important role in screening for and responding to intimate partner violence."],"references":["Russo NF, Pirlott A. Gender-based violence: concepts, methods, and findings. Ann N Y Acad Sci. 2006;1087:178-205. doi:10.1196/annals.1385.024 Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17189506/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51646"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16663"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51646","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51646"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-29T14:45:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T09:17:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9354"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66198"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroup